description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity is available for an experienced Healthcare Support Worker to join Learning &amp; Development.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking to develop your career? Are you enthusiastic, motivated with a passion to support and inspire others?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As part of the OSCE team, you will be educating aspiring Overseas Nurses across Somerset NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with other Clinical Skills Trainers, Practice Educators and the OSCE Lead you will be supporting and facilitating excellent learning opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ideal candidate will already have experience in working alongside and supporting support learners in practice, with experience of OSCE and/or Overseas Nursing a particular advantage.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Harris, OSCE Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sarah.harris@somersetft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01823 342590&lt;/p&gt;
